timeAtRisks.description: TAR 1: intention-to-treat (ITT), which followed patients until the end of data availability
TAR 3: during treatment, which followed people from 1 day after the index date until the completion of the treatment
TAR 4: during treatment with a 1-year lag

psSettings.description: PS Settings 1: 1:1 PS matching with a caliper of 0.2 SDs
PS Settings 2: variable-ratio PS matching with a maximum ratio of 1:10
PS Settings 3: PS stratification into deciles

timeAtRisks.description: TAR 5: 5-year fixed follow-up with 28-day blanking period
